that's going to be so helpful?

00:41:15.890 --> 00:41:17.200
And wise women, too.

00:41:17.200 --> 00:41:18.890
&gt;&gt; Graham Allison:
And women, yes, yes.

00:41:18.890 --> 00:41:22.690
So two people in the
current administration

00:41:22.690 --> 00:41:28.350
who were both serious students of
Thucydides, and who have looked

00:41:28.350 --> 00:41:32.110
at the book, and thought
about it are H.R. McMaster,

00:41:32.110 --> 00:41:34.460
who's Trump's National
Security Adviser.

00:41:34.460 --> 00:41:38.130
H.R. can quote more
Thucydides than anybody.

00:41:38.130 --> 00:41:42.820
He used to teach this at
Stanford, you know, College.

00:41:42.820 --> 00:41:46.050
And Jim Mattis was
a serious historian.

00:41:46.050 --> 00:41:49.630
And Thucydides is part
of his mental library.

00:41:49.630 --> 00:41:55.040
So they can understand
Thucydides's trap risks

00:41:55.040 --> 00:41:59.400
with all the else going on.

00:41:59.400 --> 00:42:05.150
They're going to have a day, and
people whom they would engage,

00:42:05.150 --> 00:42:07.470
an exercise like what happened.

00:42:07.470 --> 00:42:10.480
In the conventions of the Cold
War strategy, I don't know.

00:42:10.480 --> 00:42:12.130
We should remember
in the Cold War case,

00:42:12.130 --> 00:42:16.090
I mean the Cold War strategy
was unbelievably imaginative.

00:42:16.090 --> 00:42:19.830
And it didn't just pop out
of anybody's head one day.

00:42:19.830 --> 00:42:26.470
Kennan wrote back his famous
telegram in the spring of 1946,

00:42:26.470 --> 00:42:30.500
just a year after World War II,
saying the Soviet Union is going

00:42:30.500 --> 00:42:32.540
to be a bigger threat
than the Nazis were.

00:42:32.540 --> 00:42:36.750
It wasn't for four more years, as
people invented the Marshall Plan

00:42:36.750 --> 00:42:41.090
and NATO and the IMF and the World
Bank, and all the other elements

00:42:41.090 --> 00:42:43.720
of the Cold War strategy,
that the thing was in place.

00:42:43.720 --> 00:42:45.990
&gt;&gt; David M. Rubenstein: Now
I said earlier Robert Lovett

00:42:45.990 --> 00:42:47.290
